OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FPM's dementia adviser quits
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fover benefits clawback     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, One of the prime minister's dementia   
OL,6, champions has quit in protest over the 
OL,7, treatment of disabled people.          
OL,9,FJohnny Timpson, who was the UK's       
OL,10,Finaugural disability ambassador, said  
OL,11,Fclawing back benefits overpayments was 
OL,12,F"devastating" for families.            
OL,14,FHe was shocked by the case of a        
OL,15,F92-year-old with dementia, who was     
OL,16,Freportedly told to repay #7,000 by the 
OL,17,FDepartment for Work and Pensions (DWP).
OL,19,FThe DWP said it was committed to       
OL,20,Ffairness in the welfare system.        
